feeds.title: English 2.0 Podcast With ALsensei
feeds.description: What is the best way to learn English? How can I improve my English more quickly? If you are asking these questions, this Podcast is for you! ALsensei is an English Teaching Professional who has been helping people with how to improve English and Communication skills in Japan for over 18 years! He has worked with people from all backgrounds and levels including consulting at Global Fortune 500 companies and teaching at a prestigious university in Tokyo. However, on the English 2.0 Podcast you not only learn from ALsensei, but from other top English teachers and coaches! Al makes it a point to interview and bring you the wisdom and knowledge of other great teachers such as Luke from Luke's English Podcast, Vanessa from Speak English with Vanessa, Coach Shane from Let's Master English, Lindsay from All Ears English Podcast and many more! Whether your goal is to achieve English fluency, pass the IELTS exam, or speak English with new friends from around the world, see what English 2.0 is all about and subscribe now! Level up your learning. Level up your life.
feeds.author: Al Slagle: English Teacher, Pronunciation Coach, and Fluency Specialist

feeds.description:
Les Entrepreneurs 2.0 c'est un podcast par et pour les entrepreneurs. 
Je vais vous emmener dans des conversations en toute authencitié avec des personnalités incroyables et atypiques qui ont réussi à se créer une vie et un business selon leurs propres termes.
Depuis 2016, je vais à la rencontre d'entrepreneurs et de personnes qui me passionnent, m'impressionnent et m'inspirent. 
Mon intention avec ce podcast c'est de pouvoir vous inspirer et vous motiver à créer à votre tour une vie selon vos propres termes et de réussir à créer un business qui vous permettent de le faire.
Laissez-nous un avis et un commentaire pour donner de la visibilité à ce podcast !
Rejoignez LA TRIBU, Le meilleur business club dédié aux entrepreneurs du web

feeds.description: Join Genia in discussion with other parents, thought leaders and visionaries about helping young children with intellectual disabilities get the good things in life. Want your child to go to school, make friends, play on teams and have a bright future? Join the conversation. Good things in life is for families with vision about what is possible and how to achieve it. Whether your child has cerebral palsy, down syndrome, angelman syndrome, autism or a mild learning disability, Good Things in Life podcast can help you figure out how to take action to protect your child from harm and work towards a good life.

feeds.title: Life 2.0 podcast
feeds.description: Living with intention: Composing a life in times of accelerated change. This podcast is about ordinary people trying to find balance, harmony and purpose in everyday living. By listening to these short life stories, you will realize that the path is often messy and fragmented. Nevertheless, these ordinary people strive to live authentically and are persistent in finding ways to manifest the life they want. They learn to listen to their "gut feeling" and stay open to life. We hope you will be inspired by these journeys and encouraged to live your best life going forward! The Life 2.0 production team is comprised of enthusiastic and talented individuals: Bea Spadacini, Host, Producer and Writer; Tim Nicholson, Visual Artist and Co-Producer; Michael Balasia, Sound Engineer.

En effet, lorsque l’on est dans les temps d’attente ou les temps morts (voiture, embouteillages, en pleine mis en place du restaurant ect )le podcast est la solution pour continuer d’apprendre, de se former, d’accéder à des informations.Le Restaurateur Cast est dédié à tous les restaurateurs, qu’ils soient débutants ou confirmés ainsi qu’à tous les managers et les personnes qui sont passionnées par ce métier. Chaque épisode est en français et dure environ 15 minutes en moyenne.
